componentInstanceProperties.value:
Invest now in Nexba, Australia’s iconic Naturally Sugar Free and Functional beverage brand.


Goodness Group Global is a leader in the thriving health-conscious beverage market with our flagship brand Nexba. Over 14 years, Nexba has been at the forefront, offering $20M annually from our innovative naturally sugar-free drinks, including our renowned Nexba Kombucha. Available across 15 international markets and over 4000 grocery stores, Nexba stands out for its health benefits and exceptional taste.

Projected to achieve $31M net sales for FY25, we expect a gross profit of 24.6% with potential for significant growth and profitability, aiming for $40M net sales and $2.7M EBITDA by end of FY26. Backed by experienced leaders and major investors, Nexba is poised for rapid expansion, planning to double our sales in three years as we continue to enhance our diverse brand portfolio.


Key Investor Highlights

  • Growth: Achieving $20M in net sales this year, aiming for $40M by end of FY26 with $2.7M EBITDA, driven by partnerships with major retailers like Coles and Woolworths, and enhanced by global distribution networks.
  • Leadership: Founder-led, with a top-tier international CEO, supported by renowned Australian entrepreneurial investors and celebrities.
  • Market Opportunity: Targeting a share of the global Kombucha market projected to reach $9.6BN AUD and the broader Functional Drinks market expected at $470BN AUD by 2027.
  • Competitive Advantage: Nexba stands out with its patented ‘Goodsweet’ sweetener for great taste and low calories, underpinning the success of Goodness Group Global’s naturally sweetened products.
  • Use of Funds: Capital will boost working capital and marketing, expand Nexba’s presence in international markets and new retail channels, and support the launch of new products like PACE Sports Hydration and The Good Brekkie.

Meet the Founders

Nexba’s journey began with brothers-in-law Drew and Troy, who wanted to bring healthier drink options to Australia. Inspired by naturally sweetened iced teas enjoyed on Mexican beaches, they launched Nexba Iced Teas at Bondi within just six months.

Today, Drew leads Nexba’s operations in Australia, focusing on innovation and customer satisfaction, while Troy drives global brand marketing and expansion efforts. They are supported by David Wallwork, CEO - EMEA, a seasoned leader with over 30 years of experience in building and managing beverage brands. Together, they propel Nexba and Goodness Group Global towards international growth, leveraging their unique Goodsweet® technology.

Investor and Brand Ambassador

Pat Cummins, Aussie Cricket Captain and all round hero has joined Goodness Group Global as both investor and brand ambassador. Working closely with Pat we have developed a new Sports Hydration brand, PACE, which launches May 2024 with Pat as face of the brand and leading our extensive marketing drive as we build into this exciting new category.
